# More Control with fopen/fwrite

If you need more control (e.g., binary writes, flock), you can use `fopen()` with mode `'w'` (write, truncate) or `'x'` (create and write, fail if exists).

```php
$handle = fopen('file.txt', 'w');
fwrite($handle, 'Hello');
fclose($handle);
```

```php
<?php
$handle = fopen('newfile.txt', 'w');
if ($handle) {
    fwrite($handle, "First line\n");
    fwrite($handle, "Second line\n");
    fclose($handle);
    echo "File written.";
} else {
    echo "Cannot open file.";
}
?>
```
